title: HIGHLIGHTS | Sporting CP vs Arsenal (1-5) | UCL | Martinelli, Havertz, Gabriel, Saka, Trossard
description:
We turned in one of our best away performances in the Champions League in recent memory to secure a statement win in Lisbon.

Against the reigning Portuguese champions – unbeaten all season and second in the Champions League league phase going into the game – we netted three without reply in a dominant first half. Gabriel Martinelli and Kai Havertz put us two to the good before Gabriel headed in from a corner on the stroke of half-time.

An early second-half goal from Goncalo Inacio gave the hosts brief hope, but Bukayo Saka’s penalty and Leandro Trossard’s late goal from a parried Mikel Merino shot gave the scoreline gloss on a remarkable night in Europe.

The travelling Arsenal supporters were left to celebrate our biggest away win in the competition since beating Inter by the same score in 2003.

Another European away day, another excitable home atmosphere to try to dampen early on, and we did just that inside the opening 10 minutes. We had started really brightly, having our first attempt on goal in the first minute, but Riccardo Calafiori’s follow-up after Martinelli’s cross was half-cleared went harmlessly wide.

We continued to dictate the early play – Martin Odegaard and Bukayo Saka combined well inside the area but the hosts scrambled away the danger.

Then came the breakthrough. Jurrien Timber found space on the right, sent in a low cross that asked questions that the Portuguese defence couldn’t answer, and Martinelli stole in to score past Franco Israel and net our first away goal in the Champions League since Eddie Nketiah netted against Eindhoven in December last year.

We were good value for the lead though. Sporting – with a 100 per cent domestic record this season had barely got into our half in the first ten minutes.

It was little surprise then when we doubled the lead midway through the first half. Again the build-up came down the right, this time Thomas Partey lifted a ball over the defence for Saka to scurry onto. He stabbed the ball through the legs of the advancing keeper inside the area, and Havertz had the simple task of tapping in from a yard or two out.

The home fans started letting off fireworks inside the Estadio Jose Alvalade, but all the entertainment was being supplied by the boys in red and white. We were knocking the ball around in midfield, our movement causing no end of problems for a team that hasn’t dropped a point at home in the league since the season before last.

The locals were growing increasingly restless, not used to any visiting team dominating them in this way. Their last home game in this competition don’t forget, was a 4-1 dispatching of Manchester City.

And literally with the last touch of the first half, Gabriel made it 3-0. Declan Rice’s swerving corner from the right was just on the money for our big Brazilian defender, arriving to power in his header at the far post. It was a near-perfect first-half display.

Sporting were simply not used to being in this position, and came out with renewed determination for the second half. A minute after the restart David Raya made a full stretch save low down to deny Hidemasa Morita, and from the resulting corner Goncalo Inacio turned the ball home at the near post.

Hope for the home side, and the sound levels turned up several notches. It was our turn to come under pressure. Shortly afterwards Viktor Gyokeres won a free-kick right on the edge of the area, and took it himself, firing well over.

The momentum had swung, but in one swift moment, it was back in our favour. Odegaard broke into the area and his progress was abruptly halted by a challenge by behind from Ousmane Diomande. A penalty was awarded, and Saka stepped up to score decisively, his first away goal in the competition.

With our three-goal cushion restored, we were back in control. On came the subs and two of them combined for our fifth. Mikel Merino’s long-range shot was parried by Israel, and there was Trossard to finish off.

Ethan Nwaneri could have added a late sixth, but the job had well and truly been done by then.

title: HIGHLIGHTS Sporting CP 4-1 Man City | Foden, Gyorkeres hat-trick & Araujo goals
description:
City suffered a night of Champions League disappointment, losing out 4-1 at Sporting CP with Viktor Gyokeres hitting a hat-trick for the hosts.

Pep Guardiola’s side had got off to a flying start in Lisbon going ahead thanks to a fourth minute goal from Phil Foden.

The Blues – who handed teenage defender Jahmai Simpson-Pusey a full debut – dominated the first half carving out a host of other chances.

But, out of nowhere, Gyokeres struck to level affairs late in the first half before Sporting then scored twice within three minutes at the start of the second half through Maximiliano Araujo and Gyokeres, via a penalty, to seize control.

Watch as we compare the size and scale of the Solar System Planets with a Sports Balls comparison video for kids. Kids will be able understand the relative size of the Planets of our Solar System using balls. Space has never been as educational and fun! Watch as Planet Mars is used as a pool ball. Or biggest Planet Jupiter, uses the gym. What would Uranus think of being a baseball? Does Eris like Volleyball? And what about Earth's moon? What All this while they tell us fantastic Space, Solar System and planet facts!

Our new Channel for younger kids: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC1c5VaOm71CI3eAMqkW13ug

Toy Time Town Merch Store and latest news: www.toytimetown.com

Whichever your favourite Planet is, you will learn fun, cool facts here! Whether it is about Planets, our Solar System, Galaxy or Universe! These videos are made to entertain and educate kids equally. Each planet in our Solar System is fascinating in its own way. See what makes them such interesting planets in The Solar System, Space and the Universe. Children, families and adults alike, will find these videos about the Solar System and planets interesting and fun! As always in Toy Time Town, as well as learning, have lots of fun!

The size and scale of our Planets and Solar System is amazing. There are so many cool facts about comparing the sizes. Learn them here with Toy Time Town. Whether your favourite Planet is cheerful Earth, clever Neptune, cheeky Venus or grumpy Uranus, you will find all the planets and dwarf planets here! Educational and funny – the BEST way of learning all about Space. From kindergarten to adult, everyone will love the Toy Time Town Planets. Who is your favourite?

#PlanetComparison #VideosForKids #PlanetsKids #PlanetSizes #ToyTimeTown

title: Greatest Moments in Sports History - The Brownlee Brothers
description:
On September 18, 2016, in the final race of the World Triathlon Series in Cozumel, Mexico, Alistair Brownlee sacrificed his own race to assist his younger brother, Jonathan Brownlee. 

With less than a kilometer remaining, Jonathan, leading the race, got severe heat exhaustion - causing him to stagger and drift off course. Alistair, in second place, noticed his brother’s distress and made the selfless decision to support him. He wrapped Jonathan’s arm around his shoulders and helped him toward the finish line. In the final meters, Alistair pushed Jonathan ahead, ensuring he crossed the line in second place, while Alistair finished third. 

This act of brotherly compassion allowed Jonathan enough points to finish second in the overall series standings. The International Triathlon Union upheld the results, stating that athletes are permitted to assist fellow competitors.

#N24Carabobo #Deportes El último duelo de los eternos rivales de 2024 será hoy en el estadio José Bernardo Pérez de Valencia. Luego del emocionante duelo de anoche entre Magallanes y Caracas realizado en el estadio Monumental Simón Bolívar hoy ambos estarán en Valencia.

Este será el último duelo de la ronda regularde esta zafra, se espera una alta asistencia al estadio de la avenida Michelena. Las entradas están a la venta para aquellos que quieran presenciar este último duelo de este año.

Ambos equipos están en la lucha por un puesto en la clasificación, para vivir los emocionantes encuentros de estos dos equipos en el mes de enero. Anoche Magallanes estaba abajo en la pizarra y tuvo una épica reacción en el octavo tramo

சிங்கப்பூரில் இதுபோன்ற மேலும் பல வீடியோக்களுக்கும் வேடிக்கைகளுக்கும் எங்கள் சேனலுக்கு குழுசேர மறக்காதீர்கள்!

title: Sweeping Ice Rink For Curling #sweeping #icerink #curling #sport #sweep  #sports
description:
Sweeping Ice Rink For Curling #sweeping #icerink #curling #sport #sweep  #sports_news 

Sweeping an ice rink for curling is a crucial skill that can significantly impact a game’s outcome, allowing players to control the stone’s speed and direction. Curling may seem simple, but sweeping is a technique-heavy skill that requires coordination, strength, and strategy. Here’s everything you need to know about sweeping in curling, whether you’re just starting out or looking to improve.

Why Sweeping is Vital in Curling
In curling, sweeping plays a key role in adjusting the stone's path and distance. When you sweep, you apply friction and slightly melt the ice surface just ahead of the moving stone. This reduces resistance, letting the stone travel further and helping it stay on a straighter course. Skilled sweepers can make subtle adjustments that help their team stay on target, especially in tight scoring situations.

Choosing the Right Equipment
A good curling broom is essential for effective sweeping. Most curlers use brooms with synthetic or hair brush heads; synthetic heads tend to be more durable and efficient for intense, fast-paced sweeping. Lightweight brooms also allow for quick, powerful movements, which can make a difference in controlling the stone.

Technique: How to Sweep Effectively
Effective sweeping combines pressure, speed, and technique. To start, position yourself parallel to the stone’s path, gripping the broom with one hand near the top and the other close to the brush head. Sweep in quick, short strokes, applying consistent pressure. This combination helps keep the stone on course while maximizing its travel distance.

Practice and Team Coordination
Sweeping is a team effort. Communication with the skip, who directs the stone’s path, is essential. Practice and strength training can build endurance and help you react quickly during games. By mastering sweeping, you’ll add an invaluable skill to your curling toolkit and help elevate your team’s performance on the ice!

Yoel Yanqui vino de emergente para colocar al Magallanes en dos victorias
description:
#N24Carabobo El cubano Yoel Yanqui vino de emergente para colocar al Magallanes en dos victorias por una derrota. El antillano sacó la pelota para romper el empate a tres carreras y terminó Magallanes ganando 7×3 a Tigres de Aragua.

Los navales se fueron arriba con tres carreras gracias al cuadrangular de Renato Núñez, encontrando a dos corredores en el cierre del segundo tramo. Los turcos estuvieron arriba en la pizarra.

Pero los felinos de la ciudad jardín enseguida respondieron. José Alberto Martínez pega sencillo. Yorman Rodríguez pega infield hit y manda a Martínez a segunda. Ángel Aguilar pega doble, Martínez anota y Rodríguez avanza a tercera. Jesús Sucre recibe boleto y se llenan las bases. Alexfri plánez recibe boleto y rodríguez anota.

Tigres empató en la apertura del cuarto tramo, pero en la sexta entrada Magallanes sumó tres más. Renato Núñez pega sencillo. Alberth Martínez pega sencillo y manda a Núñez a segunda. Cambio de lanzador: sale Eiker Huizi por Christian Mejías. Y fue cuando Yanqui la sacó.

Para el cierre del octavo, Magallanes fabricó una carrera más y colocó la pizarra en 7×3. Bryan Palencia ganó, Eiker Huizi perdió, no hubo salvado para Anthony Vizcaya.

En otros resultados: Águilas del Zulia dio cuenta de Tiburones de La Guaira con pizarra de 3×2. Mientras que Bravos se impuso a Cardenales de Lara en Barquisimeto con marcador de 7×4.

title: Ski Brake And Steering #skiing #sport #sports #dangeroussports #dangeroussport #ski
description:
Ski Brake And Steering #skiing #sport #sports #dangeroussports #dangeroussport #ski 

Ski brake and steering techniques are essential for skiers of all levels to navigate slopes safely and confidently. Whether you're cruising down groomed runs or tackling challenging backcountry terrain, understanding these fundamentals can elevate your skiing experience. In this guide, we’ll dive into what makes ski brake and steering techniques so crucial and how you can master them.

What Is Ski Braking?
Ski braking refers to the techniques used to slow down or stop while skiing. It’s not just about safety; it’s also a key element of maintaining control on the slopes. The most common braking methods include:

Pizza or Snowplow Position: A classic beginner technique, where skis form a V-shape with tips together and tails apart, creating resistance to slow down.

Side Slipping: Turning skis sideways to the slope to slide downhill while controlling speed with edge pressure.

Hockey Stop: A sharp, dynamic stop where skiers turn their skis perpendicular to the slope, spraying snow as they come to a halt.

Mastering these braking techniques allows skiers to adjust speed quickly, avoid obstacles, and stop safely in emergencies.

What Is Ski Steering?
Ski steering involves controlling the direction of your skis to navigate turns, adjust your trajectory, or change your line on the slope. It’s about finesse and fluidity. Key steering techniques include:

Carving: Using the edges of your skis to make smooth, arcing turns. Carving is ideal for maintaining speed and precision on groomed slopes.

Skidding: A combination of sliding and turning, useful for sharper or slower turns.

Pole Planting: Using ski poles to guide your movements and enhance balance during turns.

Good steering techniques improve your control, stability, and overall skiing efficiency.

How to Master Ski Brake and Steering Techniques
Practice Regularly: Spend time on beginner-friendly slopes to refine your braking and steering skills.

Engage Your Core: Strong core muscles help maintain balance and control during both braking and steering maneuvers.

Seek Professional Instruction: Lessons from certified ski instructors can help you perfect your techniques and avoid common mistakes.

Renato Núñez conectó su 21° cuadrangular de la temporada e igualar la marca de Alex Cabrera
description:
#N24Carabobo Renato Núñez entró en los libros de historia de la Liga Venezolana de Béisbol Profesional (LVBP), al conectar su 21° cuadrangular de la temporada e igualar la marca de Alex Cabrera.

El bazato se produjo en un importante triunfo de la Nave ocho carreras por seis sobre Tigres de Aragua, con lo cual se mantiene en la pelea por el tercer lugar.

Aunque el cuadro turco debió venir de atrás luego de estar abajo en el marcador 6×1; logró llevarse la victoria con cuatro carreras en la séptima y tres más en el capítulo siguiente.

Renato Núñez comandó la remontada con su histórico vuelacercas en la octava entrada, productor de tres carreras, frente a los enviós del relevista Jordan Cavaneiro; mientras que Carlos Rodríguez y Tito Polo se combinaron para irse de 10-7 con cuatro anotadas.

Jesús Tinoco (2-0, 7.30) lanzó una octava entrada perfecta con par de ponches para llevare la victoria. Posteriormente, Felipe Vázquez ponchó a tres contrarios en la novena entrada para su primer rescate de la temporada.

La derrota recayó en Luis Rijo (2-2, 2.70), quien permitió que Rodríguez y Polo se embazaran en la octava entrada, antes del jonrón de Nuñez.
